  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reducing greenhouse gas emissions of the construction sector while promoting a climate-resilient built environment in Costa Rica</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under the Green Climate Fund (GCF) framework, UNIDO and the Ministry of Environment and Energy (MINAE) of Costa Rica -  GCF National Designated Authority (NDA) - are preparing a proposal for submission to the GCF Readiness and Preparatory Support Programme (RPSP). Pre-selected outcomes of the RPSP logical framework are 2.2, 2.4, 4.1, and 5.2. The purpose of the project is to develop a Readiness proposal, collect data and conduct preparatory work for the development of a full sized funding proposal and enhance national capacity required for the future project implementation.  The final project goal is to reduce emissions from the construction sector and support increased resilience of the built environment to rising temperatures in urban areas of Costa Rica. The project goal will be achieved by scaling up the use of timber as a low-emission, circular and resilient building material for the construction of social housing. The approach is based on addressing the underlying conditions for urban temperature increase, a strong consideration of the national policy framework and the country&apos;s climate priorities. The intervention will directly contribute to achieving national priorities, particularly the Nationally Determined Contribution in its contribution number 4.1, and the axis 5 of the Decarbonisation Plan 2018-20</narrative>
  </description>
